00:04:03.460 --> 00:04:06.920
One of the venture
capitalists mentioned

00:04:06.920 --> 00:04:09.390
that the difference between
a startup and a large company

00:04:09.390 --> 00:04:13.120
was, startups are
like beach volleyball.

00:04:13.120 --> 00:04:14.506
You've got two people.

00:04:14.506 --> 00:04:15.630
You don't have substitutes.

00:04:15.630 --> 00:04:16.760
You don't have coaches.

00:04:16.760 --> 00:04:18.240
You know what the game plan is.

00:04:18.240 --> 00:04:20.940
You've got to make sure the
ball doesn't touch the sand.

00:04:20.940 --> 00:04:23.960
You're playing volleyball
still, you go from two to six.

00:04:23.960 --> 00:04:28.370
All of a sudden, if Prasad
serves from the other end,

00:04:28.370 --> 00:04:30.350
I receive the serve.

00:04:30.350 --> 00:04:33.830
Bob takes it and supplies
it to Cliff, here.

00:04:33.830 --> 00:04:37.720
Cliff arcs into the air and
smashes the ball into the net.

00:04:37.720 --> 00:04:39.790
I'm sorry, Cliff.

00:04:39.790 --> 00:04:41.906
The interesting problem
is, whose fault was it?

00:04:41.906 --> 00:04:45.290
Was it Prasad's serve
that was unplayable?

00:04:45.290 --> 00:04:48.210
Was it my fault that I couldn't
receive the serve well?

00:04:48.210 --> 00:04:49.720
Or was it the way Bob supplied?

00:04:49.720 --> 00:04:51.860
Or was it Cliff's problem?

00:04:51.860 --> 00:04:54.340
So you can see, when
you go from two to six,

00:04:54.340 --> 00:04:56.880
how very quickly it
becomes a problem.

00:04:56.880 --> 00:04:59.140
And you can extend
it, six to 60,

00:04:59.140 --> 00:05:04.627
to 600, to 6,000, to
60,000, and the like.

00:05:04.627 --> 00:05:05.460
MALE SPEAKER: Great.

