00:52:21.240 --> 00:52:22.573
people to go to startups, right?

00:52:22.573 --> 00:52:23.222
[LAUGHTER]

00:52:23.222 --> 00:52:26.400
BOB SUTTON: No, no.

00:52:26.400 --> 00:52:27.394
You all know the odds.

00:52:27.394 --> 00:52:28.310
You all know the game.

00:52:28.310 --> 00:52:29.860
So it's just the way it works.

00:52:29.860 --> 00:52:32.210
So you go there, and Google
buys you or they come back,

00:52:32.210 --> 00:52:34.001
you come back as an
employee after it died.

00:52:34.001 --> 00:52:35.440
Either way, it's OK.

00:52:35.440 --> 00:52:38.100
MALE SPEAKER: So do we have time
for a question or two, Cliff,

00:52:38.100 --> 00:52:39.180
